description:

Enjoy an easy St. Paul lifestyle and listen to the Cathedral Bells!

description: For sale: $135,000. Nice location and close to hiway. Need your magic touch to make it shine again. Sell as is.

For sale: $950,000. Cass Gilbert designed, the Lightner-Young Mansion is a stately feature of the bluff side of Summit Avenue. Breathtaking views of downtown and the river valley can be taken in from 3 decks! The residence occupies the top two floors of the building and also has an additional apartment accessible by a private elevator. The main level features great entertaining space-lovely kitchen with Wolf and Sub Zero flows into the dining room with soaring vaulted ceilings and views from two decks. Beyond, find a large living room with a fireplace flanked by built-in bookshelves. Main level bedroom is currently set as a den/library. As you make your way up the open staircase, the huge stained glass skylight draws your eye to an expansive third deck off of the top floor. Master bedroom with ensuite and a third bedroom with 3/4 bath complete level. The garden level apartment features a wet bar, laundry and 3/4 bath - perfect for in-law unit or special guest space! Two car garage completes this property.

For sale: $249,900. Rare 5 bed 2 bath 2 story with loads of potential. The home features 4 bedrooms and laundry on the second level. The main floor features the 5th bedroom and a 3/4 bath. With nearly 2,000 square feet there is room to grow in this property. The home features a massive kitchen and a huge master bedroom. The two car garage is oversized and has a loft for storage. Great  opportunity to make this home your own.

description: For sale: $819,000. This beautiful brownstone truly resides in a class of it's very own! There is so much to highlight.... During seller's ownership they spared no expense to well thought out renovations and updates throughout the stunning four floors of this home. Spot on attention to natural light creates a lovely juxtaposition between dark stone exterior and BRIGHT interior, quite magical! Open and airy spaces are perfectly balanced with private wings and nooks, all flooded with natural light. description: Recently sold: $160,000.

Recently sold: $355,000. Premier Summit Avenue location. Classic Saint Paul Summit Avenue 2 bed plus den condo located in historically significant 1898 Clarence Johnston designed luxury apartment building. Top floor, elegantly proportioned rooms with 10ft ceilings and original details including decorative fireplace, hardwood floors, built-in buffet, columns, moldings and doors. Custom architect designed kitchen and bathroom renovation with high end finishes and appliances. French doors leading from living room to private tree top deck. In-unit laundry. This is a special building and a glorious home. The condo, located within the vibrant Historic Ramsey Hill neighborhood is one block from the University Club and within several blocks of 3 city parks, as well within walking distance to the great restaurants and shops of Selby and Grand Avenues. Downtown St. Paul, the St. Paul Cathedral and the Minnesota State Capitol also are all within walking distance. Urban living at its finest.

description: Recently sold: $260,000. Welcome home! This charming West Seventh craftsmen bungalow brings you that coveted vintage and character in immaculate condition, but complemented with the right tasteful updates throughout. You'll love the handsome hardwood floors, original trim & woodwork, built-in buffet, and front entry porch. The large updated open kitchen is such a rare find among this price range and era of homes. 2 updated bathrooms, industrial-chic finished basement with polished concrete floors, open exposed ceiling, and check out the marvelous beer-making station down there! The unfinished upper level brings you extra potential for yet more great space. Outside you'll find maintenance-free siding, soffits & fascia, a spacious 2.5 car garage, fully fenced yard, and a rare electric fence gate from the alley & perfect for boat storage next to the garage! Don't miss the wonderful opportunity to call this home. 2019-08-27

description:

Tranquil and private Back Yard to Garden or BBQ.  Off-Street parking - Assigned spot w/Off-Street Guest Parking Spots too.  Easy access location via 94 and 35E. Enjoy an easy St. Paul lifestyle and listen to the Cathedral Bells!

description: Recently sold: $175,000. Move-in ready classic with neutral decor and abundant natural light! This lovingly maintained home boasts 3 bedrooms, 1 bath, and an oversized, single car detached garage. Easy entertaining with a flowing floor plan and deck overlooking the lush landscaped, private back yard. Coved ceilings, gleaming hardwood floors, convenient pantry off the kitchen, and abundant storage! Basement is perfect for a workshop. Updates include: Furnace/ AC, roof, front steps, stove, refrigerator, water heater, bathroom, and windows. The wood stove is ready for those chilly winter nights!  Nestled into a historic West 7th neighborhood, just steps from shopping, dining, schools and restaurants. Easy access to 35E/94 for a quick commute. Come find your escape at day's end!

description: Recently sold: $388,000. Four-level rowhouse in the heart of Ramsey Hill. End unit with fabulous unique spaces and windows on 3 sides. Huge porch overlooking the association's private park. One of the largest row houses in the complex. 2 fireplaces (one in the owners' suite.) Soaring ceilings, open staircase, generous storage. Bath on every level. 2 blocks to WA Frost, Nina's, Red Cow, Salt Cellar, Moscow on the Hill! Right in the middle of some of the best  outdoor dining in the T.C. 2-car attached garage.

Recently sold: $260,000. Penthouse unit at St. Charles Condo's. Classic charm of a turn of the century condo, with all the modern up grades feat. spacious gourmet kitc. ss appl., granite cntrtps, center island w/gas range and breakfast bar, original hardwood floors, working fireplace, tile and granite bath, in unit laundry, designated garage spot and additional off street parking, steps to great restaurants and shops! 

Available for a August 1st move in. Please send any inquiries of 469selby.condorental@gmail.com. 

Neighborhood Description

Located in one of Saint Paul's most historic and desired neighborhoods, the St. Charles Condo is one of the best rentals available. Walk down the street to historical bars like the Happy Gnome or W.A. Frost. Enjoy the view of Saint Paul's Cathedral as you walk to historic and stunning Summit Avenue. A brief walk to Grand Ave and all the entertainment the area has to offer. Come make historic Cathedral Hill your neighborhood!
